1
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:13,099
My car's thirsty.
Can I please have some water?

2
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:30,259
God is good.
He has sent me a big, strong man.

3
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:35,497
He didn't say anything to me about it.
I was just passing.

4
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:38,134
But you did not pass.

5
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,851
That is your... your car?

6
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:49,380
That's my home.

7
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,570
You fix und dann habe ich...

8
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:56,169
I have something you do.

9
00:02:56,300 --> 00:03:01,135
I thank you very kindly, ma'am, but
I got places to go. Thanks for the water.

10
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:41,539
If it's for hire,
you got yourself one man for one day.

11
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:45,175
- Hire?
- You want me to work for you?

12
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:49,578
For hire means for money. I could build
a better fence than your girls.

13
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:54,216
Schwester Gertrude. Schwester Albertine.
Schwester Elizabeth. Schwester Agnes.

14
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:56,729
I am Mother Maria.

15
00:04:56,860 --> 00:05:01,331
Pleased to meet you all. You've got a nice
family, ma'am. My name is Homer Smith.

16
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:04,338
- Homer...?
- Homer Schmidt.

17
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:06,416
Oh, Schmidt!

18
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:13,049
Herr Schmidt, no fence.
We do that ourselves.

19
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,296
Up there. The roof.

20
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:36,152
You fix?

21
00:05:36,156 --> 00:05:37,731
It couldn't be leaking
on a day like this.

22
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:40,215
- Roof only leaks when it rains.
- Was?

23
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,331
I'm only kidding. I'll fix it good.

24
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:48,170
- You use this.
- No, thanks. I've got my own.

25
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:06,135
Can't do good work without good tools
and if you hire me, you get good work.

26
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:08,216
Hire.

27
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,368
Schwester, das Bett in die Scheune.

28
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:19,615
- What's that?
- The bed you sleep.

29
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:23,096
- No. I got my own arrangements.
- You sleep in here?

30
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:28,656
Schwester, tragen Sie die Sachen zurück
ins Haus. Schmidt schläft in seinem Auto.

31
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:31,214
No, no, you got it just a little bit wrong.

32
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:34,776
The job is finished,
so you pay me and I take off.

33
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:37,334
- Take off?
- Thatta way.

34
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:40,258
You have such a hurry?

35
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:45,579
I'm hungry. I figured I'd find me a chilli
wagon and log another hundred miles.

36
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:49,773
We were not put on the earth
to hurry, Schmidt.

37
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:52,175
For supper, I ring the bell.

38
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:58,338
Schmidt!

39
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:25,454
Jesu Christ, sei unser Gast und segne,
was du bescheret hast.

40
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,411
Amen.

41
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:31,736
Himmlischer Vater...

42
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:35,419
Möge das Essen, das du uns gibst,

43
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:40,011
Homer Schmidt stark machen,
damit er deinen Willen erfüllen kann.

44
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:43,015
- Amen.
- Amen.

45
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:07,855
Himmlischer Vater,
wir danken dir für deinen Segen.

46
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:10,289
- Amen.
- Amen.

47
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:16,448
- You folks really eating off the land.
- Was?

48
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:18,855
Er sagt, wir leben
von den Früchten des Landes.

49
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:20,936
Oh, ja! Ja!

50
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:24,451
God sets a mighty poor table.

51
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:28,572
Soon we will have vegetables too.

52
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:32,896
And sometimes chicken.

53
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,736
- Well...
- You smoke?

54
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,738
- Yes, ma'am.
- You smoke is all right.

55
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:46,175
- I think I'd better be rolling.
- Do not make hurry.

56
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:51,538
We are from Germany,
from Austria and from Hungary.

57
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:55,049
We learn English.

58
00:11:01,140 --> 00:11:05,019
Bitte senden Sie
den Diener auf mein Zimmer.

59
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:08,815
Please send the valet up to my room.

60
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:12,376
Please send the valet

61
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,458
up to my room.

62
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:18,492
Hier ist meine Wäscheliste.

63
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:22,259
Here is my laundry list.

64
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:27,172
Here is my laundry list.

65
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:33,049
Fünf Paar Socken.
Five pairs of socks.

66
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:37,617
Five pairs of socks.

67
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:39,492
Zwei Nachtkleider.

68
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:42,373
Two pyjamas.

69
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,537
Two pyjamas!

70
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:48,538
- Pyjamas!
- Hold it.

71
00:11:48,660 --> 00:11:50,730
I could speak English for you.

72
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:55,972
Warten Sie, Schwester.
Schmidt wird mit uns Englisch sprechen.

73
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:58,534
Oh, ja!

74
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,811
Sure. Anything you want to know,
just name it.

75
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:05,489
Fragen Sie ihn, was Sie wissen wollen.

76
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:10,449
What is name this?

77
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:14,490
- Phonograph.
- Phonograph.

78
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:17,737
Grammophon. Phonograph!

79
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,697
- Record.
- Record!

80
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:24,811
Phonograph record.

81
00:12:24,940 --> 00:12:27,454
Phonograph record!

82
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,378
Phonograph record is black.

83
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,697
Phonograph record is black?

84
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,253
Black?

85
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:43,294
- Stove.
- Stove!

86
00:12:43,420 --> 00:12:46,218
Stove is black.

87
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:49,377
Stove is black.

88
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:55,579
- My skin is black.
- My skin is black.

89
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:58,737
No. Her skin is white.

90
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:02,091
- My skin is black.
- White?

91
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:06,969
Weiß. White is Weiß.

92
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,250
Black is Schwarz!

93
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,735
Black is Schwarz.

94
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:14,055
No, we'd better get a... Watch me.

95
00:13:14,180 --> 00:13:17,217
- Watch me!
- No watch. No watch. Sshh.

96
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:23,299
I stand up.

97
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:27,812
I stand up.

98
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,975
I stand up!

99
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:34,459
I sit down.

100
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:37,094
I sit down.

101
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:45,649
- I stands up, ya'll.
- I stands up, y'all!

102
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:51,688
We gotta get organised.
Everybody sit down.

103
00:13:51,820 --> 00:13:54,288
Everybody sit down.

104
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,978
Everybody sit down.

105
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:03,811
Ah! Everybody sit down.

106
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:06,773
- You stand up!
- You stand up!

107
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:10,253
- You stand up.
- You sit down.

108
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:13,292
- You sit down.
- You sit down.

109
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:16,890
- We all stand up.
- We all stand up.

110
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:19,659
We all sit down!

111
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:22,817
We all sit down!

112
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:48,371
Please send a valet up to my room.

113
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:25,413
- Good night!
- Good n... Good night?

114
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:27,417
Good morning. Good morning!

115
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:32,568
Nein, nein. Guten Morgen.
Wenn Sie Deutsch sprechen wollen. Ja?

116
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,895
Good night.

117
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:38,729
- You can turn around now.
- You sleep, sleep!

118
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:41,738
Sie... Sie Faulpelz Sie!
Wissen Sie, wie spät es ist?

119
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:45,216
Die anderen arbeiten schon seit Stunden
und Sie liegen da und schlafen!

120
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:48,173
Jetzt tummeln Sie sich aber
und machen schnell!

121
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,098
You hold on one minute.

122
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:54,371
You just hold on one minute.

123
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,618
I ain't no nun.
I'm nobody you can boss around. See?

124
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:02,289
I get up when I feel like getting up
and if I don't wanna work, I don't.

125
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:06,732
Now if you just pay me, I'll be gone.

126
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:10,409
You go? No. You go eat now.

127
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:12,895
- I'll get my own chow.
- Eat!

128
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:27,215
What are you doing in here?

129
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:30,377
How come she ain't got you
digging ditches and chopping wood

130
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:32,456
and moving mountains?

131
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:35,777
Please... you slow talk?

132
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:39,496
I'm sorry.

133
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:45,409
That old lady has got a mean streak.

134
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:51,092
People have got to sleep. People
have got to have some joy in living.

135
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,654
People gotta...

136
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:55,532
eat.

137
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:01,695
That's a Catholic breakfast.

138
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,976
One egg.

139
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:10,855
That old lady don't hand out grub like
she hands out orders. Can I have coffee?

140
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:13,972
Coffee? Nein.

141
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:16,091
Ve no coffee.

142
00:17:32,980 --> 00:17:34,936
- Schmidt.
- Mama.

143
00:17:35,060 --> 00:17:39,019
We ought to get this straightened out.
I'll deduct for the dinner...

144
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:41,973
- And what you call breakfast.
- Come! Follow me.

145
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:19,773
- We build a shapel.
- It's very nice. What's a "shapel"?

146
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:23,017
Eine kleine Kirche. A cha... pel.

147
00:18:27,460 --> 00:18:30,816
- Ve build a chapel right here.
- Who's "ve"?

148
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:32,532
You.

149
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:38,013
Lots of luck. I ain't
building no "shapel".

150
00:18:38,017 --> 00:18:40,053
Ja, you.

151
00:18:40,180 --> 00:18:45,254
Not only am I ain't building no "shapel",
I'm taking off! I ain't no contractor.

152
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:47,450
- That is for the beginning.
- No.

153
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:51,651
- I don't need all that work. No.
- No? All right.

154
00:18:51,780 --> 00:18:54,169
- All right.
- We build it. We women.

155
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:57,576
- You do that little thing.
- We will. It's God's will.

156
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:59,975
Boy. Look, I'm checking out.

157
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:08,740
All right. I'll clean
out some of that stuff.

158
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:11,533
I don't want those girls
to break their backs.

159
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:15,539
Just to work off that tremendous breakfast
you fed me this morning.

160
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:17,378
- Let's settle up.
- Ja, sind Sie denn nicht zufrieden?

161
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:20,412
Wenn wir das gewusst hätten, hätten wir
Ihnen das Frühstück ans Bett gebracht.

162
00:19:20,540 --> 00:19:22,576
I hope you're not talking mean to me.

163
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:26,693
You wanted your breakfast in bed?
You talk like American millionaire!

164
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:29,288
- Yeah. That's me. A millionaire.
- Ja!

165
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:33,452
Wall Street!

166
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:54,533
"Us women, ve will build a chapel!"

167
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,292
Schmidt!

168
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:05,295
Schmidt!

169
00:20:08,660 --> 00:20:11,220
Old Mother gonna feed the slave?

170
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:21,212
Jesu Christ, sei unser Gast...

171
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:29,695
bescheret hast.

172
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:31,776
- Amen.
- Amen.

173
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:37,213
I milked the cow yesterday.

174
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:40,889
I milk the cow today.

175
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:44,569
I milk the cow tomorrow.

176
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:47,168
Very good. Very good.

177
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:49,689
- Very good, Schwester Elizabeth.
- Danke schön.

178
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:53,699
"Thank you." Thank you.
Danke schön. Thank you.

179
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:57,938
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

180
00:20:59,180 --> 00:21:01,296
- Thank you.
- Beautiful.

181
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:04,698
Now you try it, Mama. "Thank you."

182
00:21:06,180 --> 00:21:08,136
It's time.

183
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:11,216
- Good night.
- Good night.

184
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:15,851
- Good night, Sister Elizabeth.
- Good night.

185
00:21:15,980 --> 00:21:17,971
Good night, Sister Albertine.

186
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:22,730
Sister Agnes, you be up early.
You've got to milk that poor old cow.

187
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:25,738
I milk the poor old cow.

188
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:31,334
You like to make jokes, Schmidt?

189
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:37,291
This isn't exactly a joke.

190
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:40,412
Now I sit down.

191
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:42,770
I give you a bill.

192
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:46,051
You pay me for my services.

193
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:50,332
I've put in two good days here, Mother.
I'm for hire, remember? Hire.

194
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:52,735
I speak English not so good.

195
00:21:52,860 --> 00:21:56,170
You want to take advantage
of a poor country boy like me?

196
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:58,450
OK.

197
00:21:58,580 --> 00:22:00,730
OK. We'll play it your way.

198
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:11,138
Book of Luke, chapter ten, verse seven.

199
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,330
Your Bible is all in German.

200
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,534
I'll read it to you in English.

201
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:29,092
"And in the same house remain, eating
and drinking such things as they give,

202
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:33,293
for the labourer is worthy of his hire."

203
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:36,890
That's not exactly what I had in mind
but you get the idea.

204
00:22:42,580 --> 00:22:45,492
What you got there? Proverbs 14.

205
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:55,973
"Cast in thy lot amongst us,
let us all have one purse..."

206
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,979
I am a poor man! I've got to work
for wages. I can't work for...

207
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:05,329
Matthew... chapter six.

208
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:09,248
Acht und zwanzig...

209
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:11,655
Two-eight-two-nine.

210
00:23:11,780 --> 00:23:14,340
Matthew, chapter six, 28-29.

211
00:23:21,820 --> 00:23:24,175
Schmidt, read it in English.

212
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:27,731
"Why take thee thought for raiment?"

213
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:29,940
"Consider the lilies of the field
and how they grow."

214
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:31,618
"They toil not, neither do they spin,"

215
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:34,698
yet I say unto you,
not even Solomon in all his glories

216
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:36,936
"was arrayed as one of these."

217
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:39,528
Consider the lilies.

218
00:23:46,020 --> 00:23:48,488
- What's that?
- You go to bed.

219
00:23:48,620 --> 00:23:52,329
Tomorrow Sunday is.
The mass in town is nine by the clock.

220
00:23:52,460 --> 00:23:55,372
- I'm a Baptist. I don't go to mass.
- We go.

221
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:59,175
- How'd you get there before?
- We walk every Sunday. Now we got you.

222
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:01,860
Now dammit! You ain't got me!

223
00:24:01,980 --> 00:24:04,335
- Good night, Schmidt.
- Get that straight!

224
00:24:04,460 --> 00:24:06,690
- Schlafen Sie wohl.
- And cut that out.

225
00:24:06,820 --> 00:24:08,776
Bless you, Schmidt.

226
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:35,540
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

227
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:38,332
Morning.

228
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:44,894
- No breakfast?
- Never before mass.

229
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:48,332
Oh.

230
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:08,053
You guys look nice - lean, but nice.

231
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:54,216
- Where's it at?
- Was, Schmidt?

232
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:57,138
The church.

233
00:25:58,340 --> 00:26:01,332
- Yeah, but where's it at?
- Er will wissen, wo die Kirche ist.

234
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:07,857
- That's not fair.
- Over there, Schmidt.

235
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:14,453
- Now come.
- No.

236
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:16,491
I'm gonna wait in here for you.

237
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:34,694
- Are you the man?
- I am the man.

238
00:26:37,420 --> 00:26:39,376
- Can I get me some breakfast?
- Name it.

239
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:41,650
- A real breakfast?
- Whatever you say.

240
00:26:41,780 --> 00:26:44,613
Double OJ and squeeze it fresh.

241
00:26:48,220 --> 00:26:49,653
So?

242
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:56,731
A stack of wheatcakes with lots
of melted butter... maple syrup.

243
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:02,330
And fry me three, four, five eggs
with a mess of sausages

244
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:06,419
and a mountain of white toast
with strawberry marmalade

245
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:09,259
and... keep the coffee coming.

246
00:27:10,140 --> 00:27:12,449
- No beans?
- You got beans?

247
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:14,935
- The most, señor.
- Them too.

