250
00:27:33,100 --> 00:27:34,613
OK.

251
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:41,530
Very nice.

252
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:45,494
Very nice. Now...
melt some cheese over those beans.

253
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:50,497
- What's the matter you're not in church?
- I'm a Baptist.

254
00:27:50,620 --> 00:27:54,090
- Why are you working for the sisters?
- I work for myself.

255
00:27:54,220 --> 00:27:57,656
- How come you're not in church?
- I got a business.

256
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:01,853
- But you're a Catholic.
- No! I was born one, but...

257
00:28:03,340 --> 00:28:06,059
- Father Murphy...
- What's the matter with him?

258
00:28:06,180 --> 00:28:08,614
- He drinks.
- He's a priest.

259
00:28:08,740 --> 00:28:11,538
- He's Irish.
- Oh.

260
00:28:15,380 --> 00:28:17,416
Holy, holy, holy, hm?

261
00:28:17,540 --> 00:28:21,169
You pray hard enough and your stomach
doesn't feel empty any more.

262
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:25,771
Praying does not pay the rent
and praying does not fill up the gas.

263
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:29,097
God ain't gonna get behind
this counter and sling hash.

264
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:31,654
Me? I gotta fill my wallet.

265
00:28:33,580 --> 00:28:37,050
- Hey.
- What?

266
00:28:37,180 --> 00:28:39,774
- They pay you?
- Sure.

267
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:43,176
I just wondered.
I heard they don't have a cent.

268
00:28:43,300 --> 00:28:45,450
Not a cent.

269
00:28:45,580 --> 00:28:48,652
Crazy trying to farm that land.
They aren't mean enough.

270
00:28:48,780 --> 00:28:50,736
That old Mother, she'll do.

271
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:53,420
Oh-h-h!

272
00:28:54,620 --> 00:28:57,578
Old Gus Ritter -
he used to own the place.

273
00:28:57,700 --> 00:29:00,578
He could grow potatoes on bare rock.

274
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:04,772
He left the place
to this religious order in Germany.

275
00:29:04,900 --> 00:29:08,609
East Germany. The sisters
came over the Wall. They tell you that?

276
00:29:10,500 --> 00:29:13,219
- No. Like in Berlin?
- Sí.

277
00:29:13,340 --> 00:29:18,539
Over the Wall, across the ocean,
across the country to what? This.

278
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:23,971
- They can't even talk the language.
- I've been straightening them out.

279
00:29:24,100 --> 00:29:26,694
- Yeah?
- Sho'nuff!

280
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:32,695
Hey, listen. You ain't
gonna hang around with the sisters?

281
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:36,733
- Nah. I'm just passing through.
- That's right!

282
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:40,694
The sisters ask you something,
you tell them no. Keep right on going.

283
00:29:40,820 --> 00:29:43,175
- That pie there?
- Sure.

284
00:29:43,300 --> 00:29:46,417
- The whole one. Can I have it?
- It's gonna cost you.

285
00:29:46,540 --> 00:29:49,373
Wrap it. I'm a millionaire.
From Wall Street.

286
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:52,651
- My name is Homer Smith.
- Juan Aquilito.

287
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:58,138
Schmidt!

288
00:29:59,780 --> 00:30:01,213
Schmidt!

289
00:30:01,340 --> 00:30:05,128
- Schmidt!
- Looks like you're being paged.

290
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:21,089
Das ist Schmidt.
Schmidt, Father Murphy.

291
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:23,495
Father Murphy will talk with you.

292
00:30:23,620 --> 00:30:25,576
Pleased to meet you.

293
00:30:28,580 --> 00:30:31,174
Cuidado con los velos. Deprisa.

294
00:30:32,460 --> 00:30:34,894
Can we get out of this heat?

295
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:37,329
I didn't know Catholics
had outdoor meetings.

296
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:43,137
I got five other country clubs like this.
I cover about 400 miles a week.

297
00:30:46,900 --> 00:30:49,414
Welcome to the poor man's Vatican.

298
00:30:49,540 --> 00:30:50,973
Oh.

299
00:30:56,740 --> 00:31:00,255
Mother Superior tells me
she believes God sent you to her.

300
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:04,532
No. I don't think he sent
a black Baptist to a Catholic nun!

301
00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:06,696
That's what she tells me.

302
00:31:07,660 --> 00:31:11,209
She also says
you're gonna build her a chapel.

303
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:13,854
She asked me.

304
00:31:13,980 --> 00:31:17,177
But you know how it is.
I got other fish to fry.

305
00:31:17,300 --> 00:31:20,451
She believes there was a need
and she put her trust in prayer.

306
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:22,976
When I was ordained, how I prayed.

307
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:28,299
How I prayed for a call to a great majestic
cathedral in some wealthy diocese.

308
00:31:28,420 --> 00:31:31,492
I sent the message up in English,
in Latin, and he answered.

309
00:31:33,460 --> 00:31:35,212
He answered.

310
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:39,495
I baptise them,
christen them, confirm them,

311
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:43,579
hear their confessions, give absolution,
last rites, bless their remains,

312
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:47,010
fill the tank, check the oil and water,
take off again and pray.

313
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:50,496
Pray that I don't blow out
one of those old tyres.

314
00:31:50,620 --> 00:31:53,896
- You staying with the sisters?
- I'm just passing through.

315
00:31:54,020 --> 00:31:56,136
Well, I think that's for the best.

