Amen

376
00:36:43,660 --> 00:36:45,093
Schmidt!

377
00:36:46,420 --> 00:36:48,695
Two times I call you for breakfast!

378
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:51,732
I heard you. You can keep
the cup of milk and the one egg.

379
00:36:51,860 --> 00:36:55,614
You sucker me into breakfast, I'm
obliged to work. Not me. I'm cutting out.

380
00:36:55,740 --> 00:36:57,298
Was?

381
00:36:57,420 --> 00:37:01,095
This little soul is leaving the roost.
I'm heading thatta way.

382
00:37:01,220 --> 00:37:03,336
- Thatta way?
- I'm leaving.

383
00:37:04,980 --> 00:37:07,540
Schwester Gertrude, schnell!

384
00:37:07,660 --> 00:37:11,096
Hurry up! Schmidt will
take us to Northfolk!

385
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:15,209
- You take us to Northfolk.
- You got bus fare?

386
00:37:15,340 --> 00:37:17,979
- Back?
- We'll get back. Don't worry about us.

387
00:37:18,100 --> 00:37:19,692
Amen!

388
00:37:54,500 --> 00:37:59,528
Well... it's been interesting.
Not profitable, but interesting.

389
00:38:00,580 --> 00:38:02,935
Schmidt, where do you go?

390
00:38:04,300 --> 00:38:06,734
I don't know. West?

391
00:38:06,860 --> 00:38:09,693
LA, San Francisco.
Maybe I'll swing on up to...

392
00:38:14,540 --> 00:38:16,656
So... goodbye.

393
00:38:17,420 --> 00:38:21,208
- Schwester Gertrude.
- Leben Sie wohl.

394
00:39:06,580 --> 00:39:08,377
Hey, boy.

395
00:39:10,220 --> 00:39:12,176
Are you Schmidt?

396
00:39:13,260 --> 00:39:16,411
Well, that's what they call me.
My name is Homer Smith.

397
00:39:16,540 --> 00:39:20,328
Are you the fellow who's supposed
to build a chapel? They must be kidding.

398
00:39:23,020 --> 00:39:26,569
- Why?
- They tell me you're their contractor.

399
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:29,498
- So?
- Are you a contractor?

400
00:39:30,900 --> 00:39:35,291
- What's wrong with that?
- Well, what kind of contractor?

401
00:39:37,460 --> 00:39:38,734
Independent.

402
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:41,579
You local?
I don't remember doing business before.

403
00:39:41,700 --> 00:39:46,091
- I'm out of State.
- How did they get mixed up with you?

404
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:49,417
- How did they talk you into it?
- Nobody talked me into anything.

405
00:39:49,540 --> 00:39:52,373
They conned me out of some adobe brick
and some lumber.

406
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:57,369
I figured I could write that off, but
if you're their contractor, like you say,

407
00:39:57,500 --> 00:40:01,175
tell her to take her business someplace
else. My terms are strictly cash.

408
00:40:01,300 --> 00:40:04,610
- You understand, boy?
- I understand. Hey, boy!

409
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:12,095
- You need a good man?
- A good man.

410
00:40:12,220 --> 00:40:14,688
- I can give you two days a week.
- Doing what?

411
00:40:14,820 --> 00:40:17,937
- Moving earth. Those.
- You got any experience?

412
00:40:18,060 --> 00:40:20,528
I can handle any earth-moving
equipment you've got.

413
00:40:20,660 --> 00:40:22,969
What are you gonna be doing
the rest of the time?

414
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:27,252
What have we been talking about?
I'm gonna build me a chapel.

415
00:40:30,540 --> 00:40:35,011
OK, contractor. I'll pay you the going rate
for labour on the job you're assigned.

416
00:40:35,140 --> 00:40:39,975
Seven o'clock, Thursday morning. But if
you're snowing me, you'll be out at 7.15.

417
00:40:45,980 --> 00:40:47,777
Just a second.

418
00:40:52,180 --> 00:40:54,410
- Goodbye, Schmidt.
- Get in the car.

419
00:40:54,540 --> 00:40:58,499
- We go to the bus stop.
- Don't be cute.

420
00:40:58,620 --> 00:41:01,418
I don't want him to think
we're having a fuss.

421
00:41:01,540 --> 00:41:03,496
- Fuss?
- Yes. Fuss.

422
00:41:03,620 --> 00:41:05,895
You don't fuss with your contractor.

423
00:41:19,460 --> 00:41:21,416
We can do it, Schmidt.

424
00:41:22,660 --> 00:41:28,178
There are three ingredients to a job
like this. First, you need a plan. Check?

425
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:30,370
Two, you need labour.

426
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:32,456
But, three, you need materials.

427
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:38,731
That's for openers. You're gonna need 10,
20, 30, 40 times as many bricks as that.

428
00:41:40,220 --> 00:41:42,176
Can you get them?

429
00:41:44,220 --> 00:41:45,778
Ja!

430
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:50,973
OK.

431
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,934
OK. Let's get to work.

432
00:42:24,300 --> 00:42:25,892
You still listening, Lord,

433
00:42:26,020 --> 00:42:29,854
would you mind putting
a little meat on the table? Please?

434
00:42:46,140 --> 00:42:48,574
The work goes well.

435
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:51,134
The problem is money.

436
00:42:52,340 --> 00:42:55,935
I request to your organisation...

437
00:42:57,260 --> 00:43:00,616
which is renowned for its...

438
00:43:01,740 --> 00:43:04,129
- Philanthropics.
- Was?

439
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:05,739
Philanthropics.

440
00:43:05,860 --> 00:43:09,773
- Was machen Sie da, Schwester?
- Das Mittagessen für Herr Schmidt.

441
00:43:10,940 --> 00:43:13,454
Lesen Sie mir das Ganze noch mal vor.

442
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:19,337
"The Maximillian Fund,
sieben elf, Fünf Avenue, New York City.

443
00:43:19,460 --> 00:43:22,691
"Highly honoured
and respected gentlemen,

444
00:43:22,820 --> 00:43:27,177
permit me to an appeal
for financing assistance..."

445
00:43:27,300 --> 00:43:29,655
No. Wait. A better word.

446
00:43:36,780 --> 00:43:38,293
Dollars!

447
00:44:19,660 --> 00:44:21,093
- The Lions.
- Ja.

448
00:44:21,220 --> 00:44:22,812
- The Elks.
- Ja.

449
00:44:22,940 --> 00:44:26,091
- The Order of Moose.
- Ja.

450
00:44:26,220 --> 00:44:29,929
Kiwanis. What kind of animal is that?

451
00:44:30,060 --> 00:44:31,812
Americans.

452
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:41,854
Schmidt! You make knocking.
Like I told you.

453
00:44:43,140 --> 00:44:46,894
- We saved for you supper.
- No more bread and milk.

454
00:44:47,020 --> 00:44:48,817
A nice potato soup.

455
00:44:48,940 --> 00:44:52,296
Oh, and that'll make me
nice and fat and strong?

456
00:44:52,420 --> 00:44:54,490
- Ja.
- And you love me fat and strong!

457
00:44:54,620 --> 00:44:56,656
Ja.

458
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:00,856
Oh, Schnuller!

459
00:45:04,140 --> 00:45:06,700
Hey, hey. You like that.

460
00:45:25,260 --> 00:45:27,057
What now?

461
00:45:27,180 --> 00:45:29,614
Look your hands. Dirty!

462
00:45:29,740 --> 00:45:32,891
Go wash your dirty hands and face.

463
00:45:36,820 --> 00:45:39,334
OK, I will.

464
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:43,248
Then I come and give for you
the English lesson. Nein? Ja!

465
00:45:43,380 --> 00:45:45,291
Ja!

466
00:45:47,580 --> 00:45:49,935
Danke dir Gott, für diesen Segen.

467
00:45:51,780 --> 00:45:54,374
Ah, how about thanking me too, eh?

