- Everything works out.

492
00:49:08,300 --> 00:49:12,213
- I'm ready to keep going but...
- Everything works out.

493
00:49:12,340 --> 00:49:14,251
Yeah, you said that.

494
00:49:14,380 --> 00:49:18,612
- Tomorrow you for Ashton work?
- Tomorrow and the next day. Why?

495
00:49:18,740 --> 00:49:21,049
Then we see.

496
00:49:22,100 --> 00:49:26,810
- Look, we had a bargain. I kept my end...
- Everything works out. It's God's will.

497
00:49:26,940 --> 00:49:30,615
- That we get brick or that we don't?
- Whatever.

498
00:49:30,740 --> 00:49:33,971
You would have made a great lawyer,
you know that?

499
00:50:39,580 --> 00:50:41,536
Bobkin.

500
00:50:42,660 --> 00:50:44,412
Sherman.

501
00:50:45,460 --> 00:50:47,416
Good night.

502
00:50:48,540 --> 00:50:50,337
Smith.

503
00:50:50,460 --> 00:50:55,375
- Tell me, how's the contracting business?
- It's all right.

504
00:50:55,500 --> 00:50:59,095
Just out of curiosity,
what are you using for materials?

505
00:51:00,380 --> 00:51:02,848
We're expecting a new shipment.

506
00:51:42,820 --> 00:51:45,015
No bricks?

507
00:51:55,060 --> 00:51:57,858
Why do you buy things to eat
we do not need?

508
00:51:57,980 --> 00:52:00,289
Now just a minute.

509
00:52:00,420 --> 00:52:02,376
You are very large on religion

510
00:52:02,500 --> 00:52:04,968
but you don't know
how to accept a gift from somebody

511
00:52:05,100 --> 00:52:08,570
without making them feel small.
Small! You follow?

512
00:52:08,700 --> 00:52:11,339
Poor man. His feelings is hurt!

513
00:52:11,460 --> 00:52:16,170
I'm not twisting your arm for any big
thank-yous, but I'm through feeling small.

514
00:52:16,300 --> 00:52:19,417
I got all the patience in the world!

515
00:52:20,020 --> 00:52:23,808
Then why do you work on the road gang
when you should build the chapel?

516
00:52:23,940 --> 00:52:25,896
Where are the bricks?

517
00:52:27,220 --> 00:52:32,772
They will come. Maybe not tonight, but
there is other things you could be busy.

518
00:52:33,420 --> 00:52:35,729
Raking and planting trees.

519
00:52:35,860 --> 00:52:38,693
We had this contract.
You failed to keep your part.

520
00:52:39,900 --> 00:52:43,939
I failed because I put my faith in people
instead of in God!

521
00:52:44,060 --> 00:52:47,291
Forget it.
It was an invisible contract anyway.

522
00:52:47,420 --> 00:52:51,538
- I don't believe you any more.
- Who are you not to believe me?

523
00:52:51,660 --> 00:52:56,131
Hm?! Somebody
passing through thatta way?

524
00:52:56,260 --> 00:53:00,219
Me, I come 8,000 miles to this place.

525
00:53:00,340 --> 00:53:04,253
You cry about a few bricks
which are not here when you want them!

526
00:53:04,380 --> 00:53:07,736
Do you know what we went through
to get to this place?

527
00:53:08,980 --> 00:53:11,335
You will not
stand in the way of this chapel.

528
00:53:11,940 --> 00:53:15,410
No. It will be done.

529
00:53:16,020 --> 00:53:18,739
Well, good luck, Charlie,
and you deal me out.

530
00:53:19,580 --> 00:53:21,491
Yeah. That stuff you wear,

531
00:53:21,620 --> 00:53:24,339
you think it's a uniform
that makes you some kind of cop,

532
00:53:24,460 --> 00:53:27,577
laying down the law,
throwing your weight around.

533
00:53:27,700 --> 00:53:32,979
You sound like one of them
old war movies. A regular Hitler!

534
00:53:38,020 --> 00:53:41,979
Well, you get yourself another boy.

535
00:54:20,500 --> 00:54:24,778
Mutter Maria! Hat der Schmidt
seinen Hammer daeglassen?

536
00:54:24,900 --> 00:54:28,495
Nein! He left nothing. Nothing!

537
00:54:28,620 --> 00:54:30,656
Das haben wir nötig gehabt.

538
00:54:30,780 --> 00:54:35,092
Zuerst beten wir für ihn, dann kommt er
und dann shickt sie ihn weg.

539
00:54:42,580 --> 00:54:44,536
Nothing.

540
00:55:38,380 --> 00:55:41,417
- You haven't heard anything from Smith?
- Nein. Nothing.

541
00:55:41,540 --> 00:55:44,976
- It's been three weeks.
- We thought at least he write postcard...

542
00:55:45,100 --> 00:55:48,297
Schweigen Sie, Schwester.
He will return.

543
00:55:48,420 --> 00:55:52,299
You're sure of that? Well, I wouldn't
get too upset about it, ma'am.

544
00:55:52,420 --> 00:55:55,730
He's shiftless and irresponsible,
you know the type?

545
00:55:55,860 --> 00:55:59,535
If he should come back, tell him
I'll hold his job open for a while.

546
00:55:59,660 --> 00:56:02,572
He's a pretty good man with a bulldozer.

547
00:57:58,220 --> 00:58:00,893
Smile at the people.

548
00:58:03,820 --> 00:58:06,175
But don't say anything.

549
00:58:08,820 --> 00:58:10,776
Go get your breakfast.

550
00:58:17,380 --> 00:58:19,336
Good morning.

551
00:58:20,540 --> 00:58:22,496
Good morning.

552
00:58:23,540 --> 00:58:25,690
Such a beautiful morning.

553
00:58:40,620 --> 00:58:44,249
Business Sunday morning
seems to have gotten better since I left.

554
00:58:44,380 --> 00:58:46,894
A question. Why?

555
00:58:47,020 --> 00:58:49,978
- Why did I take off?
- No. Why you come back?

556
00:58:52,580 --> 00:58:55,253
What's it to you?

557
00:58:59,660 --> 00:59:03,175
Sí. Sí. Sí. Gracias.

558
00:59:03,300 --> 00:59:06,212
- Now you have done it.
- Hm?

559
00:59:06,340 --> 00:59:10,891
That was a messenger. They
want to know if you are back to stay.

560
00:59:11,020 --> 00:59:16,219
I have told them yes. I make them happy.
Now you have the big breakfast, eh?

561
00:59:16,860 --> 00:59:19,420
What will it be?

562
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:23,256
A coke.

563
00:59:27,060 --> 00:59:31,019
"Wash yourself, Schmidt.
Vash away ze stink."

564
00:59:35,340 --> 00:59:40,812
Why didn't they ask me to build
a bath tub with nice hot water?

565
00:59:42,220 --> 00:59:45,895
That'd make more sense.
"Wash yourself, Schmidt."

566
00:59:53,460 --> 00:59:57,009
That's the first kind word I've had
since I got back.

567
01:00:01,260 --> 01:00:04,935
What bugs me, she was so positive
I was coming back.

568
01:00:06,540 --> 01:00:09,816
You wouldn't happen to have
a nice cold can of beer on you?

569
01:00:13,180 --> 01:00:15,216
I must be out of my skull coming back.

570
01:00:17,220 --> 01:00:18,972
Schmidt!

571
01:00:20,620 --> 01:00:22,576
Schmidt!

572
01:00:31,540 --> 01:00:35,658
Schmidt, look, all these bricks!
Isn't it glorious?

573
01:00:36,900 --> 01:00:38,492
Gracias.

574
01:00:43,340 --> 01:00:45,296
Faulpelz. Lassen Sie doch die...

575
01:00:45,420 --> 01:00:48,457
- Don't work them by themselves.
- This isn't enough.

576
01:00:48,580 --> 01:00:50,969
- All right.
- All right? What?

577
01:00:51,100 --> 01:00:53,056
We pray some more!

578
01:01:24,460 --> 01:01:27,452
- We have come to help you.
- Thanks.

579
01:01:28,500 --> 01:01:31,537
I thank you very much,
but I don't need any help, thank you.

580
01:01:42,380 --> 01:01:45,975
You are sure
you are doing the right thing?

581
01:01:48,140 --> 01:01:50,176
You prayed up a lot of bricks, Mama,

582
01:01:50,300 --> 01:01:53,497
but you only prayed for one man
to build your chapel.

583
01:02:20,140 --> 01:02:25,089
Hey, amigo. I had to come see
the one-man cathedral.

584
01:02:26,460 --> 01:02:31,693
This is all you have done in one week?
God made the whole world in that time.

585
01:02:31,820 --> 01:02:34,129
And he was able to rest.

586
01:02:35,660 --> 01:02:38,254
Hey. Notice your audience.

587
01:02:40,060 --> 01:02:44,372
- I can't get rid of 'em.
- They heard it was the best show in town!

588
01:03:15,180 --> 01:03:18,092
Está bien para UN americano.

589
01:03:49,340 --> 01:03:51,854
Move your foot off my adobe.

590
01:03:54,700 --> 01:03:58,329
Where would you like us to bury you?
Under the altar?

591
01:03:58,460 --> 01:04:00,416
Move your foot off my adobe.

592
01:04:49,340 --> 01:04:55,210
You do not want it? Do not take it.
Step over it and go get another one.

593
01:06:36,140 --> 01:06:38,370
A piece of pie?

594
01:06:39,620 --> 01:06:41,338
I'm not hungry.

595
01:06:41,460 --> 01:06:44,179
Was ist los mit dem? Was ist?

596
01:06:46,780 --> 01:06:49,169
I wanted to build it myself.

597
01:06:49,300 --> 01:06:52,656
Those people help you and all is well.

598
01:06:52,780 --> 01:06:57,171
I don't want any help.
I wanted to build it myself.

599
01:06:57,300 --> 01:07:00,292
That way it would be built
slowly and carefully.

600
01:07:00,420 --> 01:07:04,015
So now it's fast and it's ready the sooner.

601
01:07:04,140 --> 01:07:06,096
The Archbishop...

602
01:07:07,460 --> 01:07:12,011
If he is busy, he will not come
but I think we should invite him.

603
01:07:13,380 --> 01:07:14,813
Look...

604
01:07:15,860 --> 01:07:20,172
You see, all my life,
I wanted to really build something.

605
01:07:23,140 --> 01:07:27,213
Maybe if I had had an education I would
have been an architect or an engineer -

606
01:07:27,340 --> 01:07:31,731
throw the Golden Gate Bridge
across San Francisco Bay.

607
01:07:31,860 --> 01:07:35,250
And even maybe
build a rocket ship to Venus.

608
01:07:40,740 --> 01:07:43,015
I'm not getting through to you.

609
01:07:43,140 --> 01:07:48,294
Well, the chapel is being built
and that's all that matters.

610
01:07:49,980 --> 01:07:52,699
I wanted to build it myself.

611
01:07:55,860 --> 01:07:58,169
God is building out there the chapel

612
01:07:58,300 --> 01:08:02,088
and you sit here feeling sorry for yourself
because you are not Him?

613
01:08:05,100 --> 01:08:06,533
Ah.

614
01:08:18,420 --> 01:08:20,490
He did not finish den Kaffee.

615
01:08:33,140 --> 01:08:35,495
You build the walls too high.

616
01:08:37,100 --> 01:08:40,490
Die Mauern. Die Mauern... zu hoch.

617
01:08:40,620 --> 01:08:45,489
Der Balken - nicht dort, da anfangen.
Verstehen Sie mich?

618
01:08:45,620 --> 01:08:47,770
Necesitamos para el marco DE la ventana.

619
01:08:47,900 --> 01:08:50,255
Es ist ja ganz egal, was Sie sagen.

620
01:08:50,380 --> 01:08:54,851
Es ist kein Platz für den Beichtstuhl
und das Weihwasser vorgesehen.

621
01:08:54,980 --> 01:08:59,770
Mother Maria, no comprende
sus instrucionnes.

622
01:08:59,900 --> 01:09:01,936
Das ist nicht richtig. Verstehen Sie?

623
01:09:05,860 --> 01:09:08,897
Aber das ist nicht richtig.
Verstehen Sie?

624
01:09:14,900 --> 01:09:17,573
Deswegen hat die Mutter Maria gesagt,
wir müssen...

625
01:09:26,660 --> 01:09:32,769
Ah, Francesco.
Der Wanden is for support. The wall.

626
01:09:34,420 --> 01:09:36,650
Madre mia! What am I doing here?

627
01:09:40,820 --> 01:09:42,412
Amigo!

628
01:09:49,100 --> 01:09:52,092
Everybody. Everybody! Everybody!

629
01:09:52,220 --> 01:09:54,734
It is wrong... was ihr macht.

630
01:09:54,940 --> 01:09:59,013
Eine Kirche is for Beten. Beten.

631
01:09:59,140 --> 01:10:03,691
Look, you promised them a chapel,
now they will have nothing. Nada.

632
01:10:03,820 --> 01:10:06,618
With practically application.

633
01:10:06,740 --> 01:10:10,415
So... Oh, do not stop now.

634
01:10:11,420 --> 01:10:14,298
OK, OK. I thought you was loco.

635
01:10:14,420 --> 01:10:17,298
I was wrong. You was right.

636
01:10:18,340 --> 01:10:22,856
See, I have the big humility, amigo.
How about you?

637
01:10:25,660 --> 01:10:29,175
The walls are high too much.

638
01:10:30,940 --> 01:10:33,215
The padre was right.

639
01:10:33,340 --> 01:10:37,731
You quit, they go home,
the walls fall down,

640
01:10:37,860 --> 01:10:40,055
the rain, she melts the bricks,

641
01:10:40,180 --> 01:10:43,331
the wind, she blows away the dust.

642
01:10:43,460 --> 01:10:46,691
They will be back
getting their spiritual comfort

643
01:10:46,820 --> 01:10:49,380
from the back end of a pie wagon.

644
01:10:49,500 --> 01:10:53,379
Come!
Please come back like it was.

645
01:10:53,500 --> 01:10:58,210
Everyone working together
and laughing and singing!

646
01:10:58,340 --> 01:11:00,695
And that's the way how it should be!

647
01:11:03,660 --> 01:11:06,049
Hold it!

648
01:11:06,180 --> 01:11:08,136
Everything is cockeyed.

649
01:11:08,260 --> 01:11:11,411
That beam - Mario, Pedro -
it belongs there.

650
01:11:11,540 --> 01:11:15,613
Here's the way it goes. That beam
sits on a joist and it supports the roof.

651
01:11:15,740 --> 01:11:18,174
- You got it?
- Sí.

652
01:11:18,300 --> 01:11:20,689
And the walls are not high enough.

653
01:11:20,820 --> 01:11:24,859
- Jesus, we need more adobe all around.
- Sí, señor.

654
01:11:24,980 --> 01:11:27,050
- Some boss, eh?
- Sí.

655
01:11:27,180 --> 01:11:29,171
A job needs a boss
who knows what he's doing.

656
01:11:29,300 --> 01:11:32,337
I'm no boss, but I just know
how I want my chapel built.

657
01:11:32,460 --> 01:11:36,533
Felipe, once we get that beam in place,
we're gonna pitch the roof, yeah?

658
01:11:36,660 --> 01:11:40,050
- Like this. You follow?
- El boss!

659
01:11:44,300 --> 01:11:47,736
All right. Vamanos.
Let's get this show on the road.

660
01:11:47,860 --> 01:11:51,136
Let's go. Girls, these men
are gonna need food - lots of it.

661
01:11:51,260 --> 01:11:54,889
So start squeezing that cow
and buttering up those sandwiches.

662
01:11:55,020 --> 01:11:57,295
More adobe in here! Let's go!

663
01:11:57,420 --> 01:11:59,376
You too, Mama. Macht schnell!

664
01:11:59,500 --> 01:12:01,456
A Hitler.

665
01:12:41,500 --> 01:12:42,933
Adobe.

666
01:12:43,060 --> 01:12:45,813
This was made for ten thousand years.

667
01:12:45,940 --> 01:12:48,329
- Feel good!
- Ja!

668
01:12:48,460 --> 01:12:50,735
- Boss wants more adobe.
- Ja.

669
01:12:50,860 --> 01:12:52,816
Where is the boss?

670
01:13:11,500 --> 01:13:14,697
Hey, put another man on this beam!
Miguel!

671
01:13:14,820 --> 01:13:17,539
I need you topside to tie off this truss.

672
01:13:21,820 --> 01:13:24,459
Easy does it. Hold it there.

673
01:13:24,580 --> 01:13:26,536
Hold it there.

674
01:13:27,580 --> 01:13:31,812
Oh, hello... Get up there and tie off
that side. He'll be up in a second.

675
01:13:31,940 --> 01:13:35,296
- I heard about this in town.
- Yeah, you did?

676
01:13:36,340 --> 01:13:39,776
- Juan, think the barbecue's ready?
- Oh, sí. Sí, señor.

677
01:13:39,900 --> 01:13:42,972
- Let them tie off this, then call lunch.
- OK, boss.

678
01:13:43,100 --> 01:13:45,056
Some boss!

679
01:13:45,180 --> 01:13:48,172
Muchachos! Lunch! Lunch!

680
01:13:50,100 --> 01:13:52,056
Lunch! Lunch!

681
01:14:02,380 --> 01:14:05,258
Say, where'd you get all the materials?

682
01:14:05,380 --> 01:14:08,452
- The people give them, señor.
- What for?

683
01:14:08,580 --> 01:14:10,730
A man he gives wood, bricks.

684
01:14:10,860 --> 01:14:13,294
This time, what does he get? A chapel.

685
01:14:13,420 --> 01:14:16,412
A place where his children
can receive the sacraments.

686
01:14:16,540 --> 01:14:19,259
For their children to have faith,
it is important.

687
01:14:19,380 --> 01:14:23,419
- Is that why you're here?
- To me, it is insurance.

688
01:14:23,540 --> 01:14:28,409
To me, life is here on this earth. I cannot
see further so I cannot believe further.

689
01:14:28,540 --> 01:14:33,819
But if they are right about the hereafter,
I have paid my insurance, señor.

690
01:14:35,340 --> 01:14:36,455
Hey, boss!

691
01:14:43,820 --> 01:14:47,654
- Is there something I can do for you?
- Well, I'm kind of short-handed.

692
01:14:47,780 --> 01:14:49,736
Getting good labour is always a problem.

693
01:14:49,860 --> 01:14:52,010
Oh, really?

694
01:14:52,140 --> 01:14:54,370
Er, I've got a new freeway deal.

695
01:14:55,420 --> 01:14:57,980
Sorry, Mr Ashton,
but I've got a church contract.

696
01:14:58,100 --> 01:15:01,251
Well, when you're finished,
I could use a foreman, Mr Smith.

697
01:15:04,140 --> 01:15:09,453
Thanks, Mr Ashton. But when
I'm finished here, I'll be moving on.

698
01:15:09,580 --> 01:15:11,332
- But thanks.
- Señor Homer?

699
01:15:14,740 --> 01:15:16,332
Oh.

700
01:15:17,060 --> 01:15:22,009
Well, we're gonna have to find
a very special place to put that!

701
01:15:22,140 --> 01:15:24,096
Thank you. Thank you.

702
01:15:26,500 --> 01:15:29,094
You'd better take this to Mother Maria.

703
01:15:32,060 --> 01:15:34,016
Everybody wants to give.

704
01:15:38,460 --> 01:15:40,928
Hey, mister. Mister.

705
01:15:41,060 --> 01:15:43,779
Today we raise the roof.
We have fiesta. You come?

706
01:15:43,900 --> 01:15:46,619
Oh. No. No, thanks.

707
01:15:46,740 --> 01:15:49,538
I've got something I have to do,
but thanks.

708
01:15:49,660 --> 01:15:51,412
DE nada. Adios.

709
01:16:10,700 --> 01:16:15,251
"Und Gott war das Wort..."

710
01:16:51,780 --> 01:16:56,092
Dieser verrückte Schmidt
und seine verrückten Freunde.

711
01:16:56,220 --> 01:16:58,688
Perdónelos, madre,
que todos son unos borrachos.

712
01:16:58,820 --> 01:17:01,937
They build a house, a barn,
there's always a fiesta.

713
01:17:02,060 --> 01:17:05,018
Fiesta! In my chapel!

714
01:17:11,780 --> 01:17:14,374
Gringo man!

715
01:17:15,780 --> 01:17:19,170
Gringo! I don't know
if that's a step up or a step down

716
01:17:19,300 --> 01:17:22,019
from somethin' else
I've been called all my life!

717
01:17:36,900 --> 01:17:40,415
- Well, you are awake?
- I guess so.

718
01:17:40,540 --> 01:17:41,973
Good.

719
01:17:44,780 --> 01:17:46,452
Why'd you do that?

720
01:17:46,580 --> 01:17:49,538
The women last night
say that is the only thing

721
01:17:49,660 --> 01:17:53,130
when a man has been mixing wine
with tequila.

722
01:17:53,260 --> 01:17:55,694
I'm gonna mix you... With tequila!

723
01:18:09,940 --> 01:18:12,659
Por favor, shut that thing off!

724
01:18:12,780 --> 01:18:16,250
Morning! I've brought
something over for your chapel.

725
01:18:17,300 --> 01:18:20,337
They're seconds but I figured
you could use them somewhere.

726
01:18:20,460 --> 01:18:23,770
- They were taking up space at the yard.
- What do you think?

727
01:18:23,900 --> 01:18:27,051
We could crush 'em.
Use them for gravel for the wall.

728
01:18:27,180 --> 01:18:32,095
But those are worth... I mean...
Well, they've been fired good and strong.

729
01:18:34,140 --> 01:18:36,813
- Thanks.
- Mr Ashton!

730
01:18:36,940 --> 01:18:38,692
Mr Ashton!

731
01:18:41,460 --> 01:18:44,418
I should have sent those bricks over
anonymously.

732
01:18:44,540 --> 01:18:50,331
He's very generous - he sees we're
building with adobe, he gives us bricks.

733
01:18:50,460 --> 01:18:53,418
They're very expensive.
I wonder what made him do it.

734
01:18:53,540 --> 01:18:56,008
- Insurance.
- What?

735
01:18:56,140 --> 01:18:57,892
Forget it.

736
01:19:00,020 --> 01:19:03,695
Mr Ashton, we need bricks,
we need lumber,

737
01:19:03,820 --> 01:19:07,449
we need shingles and plenty of cement.

738
01:19:07,580 --> 01:19:10,094
Because we will build a school
and a hospital.

739
01:19:10,220 --> 01:19:14,179
And we need beams please, Mr Ashton.
Do you understand?

740
01:19:19,460 --> 01:19:21,416
Hey, Smith.

741
01:19:28,780 --> 01:19:33,012
You and getting everybody involved.
You've been making a lot of mischief.

742
01:19:33,140 --> 01:19:35,210
- What's the matter?
- She's really after me.

743
01:19:35,340 --> 01:19:39,379
- But the chapel's almost finished.
- Oh, no. She's just beginning.

744
01:19:39,500 --> 01:19:41,809
Next she'll want a school, then a hospital

745
01:19:41,940 --> 01:19:44,090
and only God knows - and she -
what comes next.

746
01:19:44,220 --> 01:19:49,135
Only so much is deductible.
She's gonna be on my back from now on!

747
01:19:49,260 --> 01:19:51,216
That sweet old lady?

748
01:20:00,180 --> 01:20:04,014
- Señor Boss, can I help you?
- No, gracias. This part is mine.

749
01:20:04,140 --> 01:20:06,096
This part is mine.

750
01:21:09,220 --> 01:21:11,688
Señor Smith? Will it have bells?

751
01:21:11,820 --> 01:21:13,776
Sure. Some day.

752
01:22:16,020 --> 01:22:17,533
So...

753
01:22:19,540 --> 01:22:21,132
So.

754
01:22:21,260 --> 01:22:23,569
Tomorrow, the first masses.

755
01:22:25,300 --> 01:22:27,291
See...

756
01:22:27,420 --> 01:22:29,650
Seat in the front. You.

757
01:22:29,780 --> 01:22:31,975
Where all the people can see you.

758
01:22:33,660 --> 01:22:37,130
And every one of these bricks
over the door I put in myself.

759
01:22:49,260 --> 01:22:53,731
A real church for you to say the mass.
Es verdad, padre?

760
01:23:15,220 --> 01:23:18,257
There is so much to do. So much to do.

761
01:23:19,420 --> 01:23:23,015
Tomorrow from Northfolk
the town choir is coming.

762
01:23:23,140 --> 01:23:28,612
The boys and girls. Such beautiful voices
you never have heard.

763
01:23:28,740 --> 01:23:30,571
Forgive me.

764
01:23:31,700 --> 01:23:34,772
They will stand over there
and up there flowers.

765
01:23:34,900 --> 01:23:39,098
On both sides of the altar, flowers.
Nothing but flowers.

766
01:23:39,220 --> 01:23:41,780
I have much to do. Much to do.

767
01:23:41,900 --> 01:23:47,213
Many years ago, I made
a very vain and selfish prayer.

768
01:23:48,060 --> 01:23:52,736
Now He has answered my prayer
through you, through many people.

769
01:23:54,660 --> 01:23:58,938
I... I pray now I become worthy
of His trust and yours.

770
01:24:00,620 --> 01:24:04,329
I have so much to do. So much to do.

771
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:33,655
Ave Maris Stella

772
01:24:34,020 --> 01:24:38,491
Dei Mater alma

773
01:24:38,620 --> 01:24:44,809
Atque semper virgo

774
01:24:44,940 --> 01:24:49,138
Felix coeli porta

775
01:24:49,260 --> 01:24:54,288
Amen

776
01:24:57,740 --> 01:25:00,493
Do you feel all right?

777
01:25:01,860 --> 01:25:06,980
- Tonight you not smile, Herr Schmidt.
- Come on, smile.

778
01:25:07,100 --> 01:25:10,137
This is like the first night you come, ja?

779
01:25:10,780 --> 01:25:13,248
- Schmidt!
- Nothing's changed.

780
01:25:14,300 --> 01:25:15,733
Schmidt.

781
01:25:17,620 --> 01:25:21,056
You did not fasten the pews to the floor...

782
01:25:21,180 --> 01:25:23,535
It's done.

783
01:25:23,660 --> 01:25:26,857
You must oil the doors
so they will not squeak in the mass.

784
01:25:26,980 --> 01:25:29,175
It's done.

785
01:25:29,300 --> 01:25:31,355
But the rail of the
altar you did not fix.

786
01:25:31,359 --> 01:25:33,418
Everything is done.

787
01:25:47,460 --> 01:25:50,497
- Ja?
- Ja.

788
01:25:54,940 --> 01:25:57,738
Then it is all finished.

789
01:25:58,340 --> 01:26:03,334
It's all finished.
I done builded you a "shapel".

790
01:26:04,060 --> 01:26:08,178
You built me a... cha-pel.

791
01:26:08,940 --> 01:26:11,249
Correction. S-ank you.

792
01:26:11,380 --> 01:26:16,500
Correction. Th-ank you...

793
01:26:20,180 --> 01:26:22,648
That's very nice.

794
01:26:27,900 --> 01:26:30,698
Well, it's English lesson time.

795
01:26:32,500 --> 01:26:36,209
- I built a chapel.
- I built a chapel.

796
01:26:36,340 --> 01:26:39,650
- You built a chapel.
- You built a chapel.

797
01:26:39,780 --> 01:26:43,534
- Oh, we built a chapel.
- We built a chapel.

798
01:26:43,660 --> 01:26:46,697
He built the chapel.

799
01:26:47,300 --> 01:26:48,938
Amen!

800
01:26:49,060 --> 01:26:50,288
Amen.

801
01:26:50,420 --> 01:26:51,648
Ay-men.

802
01:26:51,780 --> 01:26:54,248
Ay-men!

803
01:26:54,380 --> 01:26:57,213
Amen

804
01:26:57,340 --> 01:27:00,252
Amen

805
01:27:00,380 --> 01:27:02,496
Amen

806
01:27:02,620 --> 01:27:06,454
Amen, amen Sing it over

807
01:27:06,580 --> 01:27:09,492
Amen

808
01:27:09,620 --> 01:27:12,339
Amen

809
01:27:12,460 --> 01:27:14,576
Amen

810
01:27:14,700 --> 01:27:18,579
Amen, amen See the baby

811
01:27:18,700 --> 01:27:21,658
- Amen.
- Wrapped in a manger

812
01:27:21,780 --> 01:27:24,578
- Amen.
- On Christmas morning

813
01:27:24,700 --> 01:27:28,409
Amen, amen

814
01:27:28,540 --> 01:27:30,735
- Amen.
- See him in the temple

815
01:27:30,860 --> 01:27:33,818
- Amen.
- Talking with the elders

816
01:27:33,940 --> 01:27:36,852
- Amen.
- Who marvel at his wisdom

817
01:27:36,980 --> 01:27:42,771
- Amen, amen, amen.
- Down at the Jordan

818
01:27:42,900 --> 01:27:45,892
- Amen.
- Where John was baptising

819
01:27:46,020 --> 01:27:48,739
- Amen.
- And saving all sinners

820
01:27:48,860 --> 01:27:55,015
- Amen, amen, amen.
- See him at the seaside

821
01:27:55,140 --> 01:27:57,893
- Amen.
- Talking with the fishermen

822
01:27:58,020 --> 01:28:00,818
- Amen.
- And making them disciples

823
01:28:00,940 --> 01:28:06,890
- Amen, amen, amen.
- Marching in Jerusalem

824
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:10,012
- Amen.
- Over palm branches

825
01:28:10,140 --> 01:28:12,938
- Amen.
- In pomp and splendour

826
01:28:13,060 --> 01:28:18,976
- Amen, amen, amen.
- See him in the garden

827
01:28:19,100 --> 01:28:22,092
- Amen.
- Praying to his father

828
01:28:22,220 --> 01:28:25,053
- Amen.
- In deepest sorrow

829
01:28:25,180 --> 01:28:31,176
- Amen, amen, amen.
- Led before Pilate

830
01:28:31,300 --> 01:28:34,372
- Amen.
- Then they crucified him

831
01:28:34,500 --> 01:28:37,412
- Amen.
- But he rose on Easter

832
01:28:37,540 --> 01:28:43,490
- Amen, amen, amen.
- Hallelujah!

833
01:28:43,620 --> 01:28:46,578
- Amen.
- He died to save us

834
01:28:46,700 --> 01:28:49,737
- Amen.
- And he lives forever

835
01:28:49,860 --> 01:28:55,651
- Amen, amen, amen.
- Hallelujah!

836
01:28:55,780 --> 01:28:58,169
Amen

837
01:28:58,300 --> 01:29:00,097
Amen

838
01:29:00,220 --> 01:29:04,008
Amen!

